{"id": "ceac04e5900630c5a3ea4b5911ad13bc5b3266286bd28c8cae1fd27c3b4ad68c", "item_id": "56c4761219:0", "text": "Pivot Center"}
{"id": "8bcee6e42fd4e6509bc1c577e87f2818c1be5cff342d09d2268f4e19350d6b1f", "item_id": "56c4761219:1", "text": "Point (relative to focal plane and center-of-frame) where no dof distorion occurrs."}
{"id": "e5ea162e609056890a100b443b55988db406e8ffef46c4f743a70d7ccd38097d", "item_id": "56c4761219:2", "text": "Radius Strength"}
{"id": "c9e5ea3729fb390a82a284a1593b320edd1113ef72e098caba08774b5c02b4bb", "item_id": "56c4761219:3", "text": "Strength of depth of field radial effect."}
{"id": "06149d700bab27f71a233da252e8b98fadc421ab7506ac242a0e3084a2dfc9b3", "item_id": "56c4761219:4", "text": "Radius Falloff"}
{"id": "860b78b58f71f15cfb2e82f2a7edef5e9f32c11c51d463e3495eab37598eb696", "item_id": "56c4761219:5", "text": "Sharpness of depth of field radial effect."}
{"id": "0e3152d396c4ed11355a06bf640820815f56ebba1197a13cd489319b5e237a0f", "item_id": "56c4761219:6", "text": "Squeeze Center"}
{"id": "9640e3145ae676bebe868befdd5b244f5f85bafcc2bb7c60470f020c5a361462", "item_id": "56c4761219:7", "text": "Point (relative to focal plane and center-of-frame) corresponding to the center of the DOF squeeze effect."}
{"id": "e1726e32c463a941f0b23bc905f08061b52ad91583f383c39d011cf2b6b7fab2", "item_id": "56c4761219:8", "text": "Squeeze Strength"}
{"id": "ffda4322f22175cfd82ebd35ada27703388aaaba928328fb8db89130635052b4", "item_id": "56c4761219:9", "text": "Strength of DOF \"squeeze\" effect. Positive values squeeze along the circumference; negative values squeeze along the radius. 0 is off"}
{"id": "c9403894ada1ac99c2a6bfced10a6cad262e967b9a0ebeb869fea277ce0e0c7e", "item_id": "56c4761219:10", "text": "Squeeze Anamorph"}
{"id": "52e214054c96d6da5dde975dd71e14317a8d1d169774a338c6ccc0a335cd49f2", "item_id": "56c4761219:11", "text": "Anamorphic aspect ratio of radial dof \"squeeze\" effect."}
{"id": "214701d3bd5247800686cf52d059dde6e84ac4f0c80305c9893ad6716216c006", "item_id": "56c4761219:12", "text": "Squeeze Falloff"}
{"id": "fec0bee9143d42358888c2bf4a8ef639c5c5c492cebe07b5cb1fbe2c10989abd", "item_id": "56c4761219:13", "text": "Radial strength falloff of the DOF \"squeeze\" effect. Larger numbers correspond to sharper falloff. Negative values are valid."}
{"id": "548e81b57a703f6f68cceaceb2bc95b0da4c91cc9ad94c170168715b84a9983c", "item_id": "56c4761219:14", "text": "DOF Multiplier"}
{"id": "c57605aed89675d96d2c83f1254687fb4445047874582db0ef6b7c1441afd02a", "item_id": "56c4761219:15", "text": "Global multiplier on depth of field."}
{"id": "0605a0da38e920f6cd88c53887501b3e54f14bada76d696fa590e1156635a404", "item_id": "56c4761219:16", "text": "Circle of Confusion Texture"}
{"id": "93230e3155ec9f6ed27d2b7e589fb5ac8600a0150fd6f2bba2c2e91d0dbcff4b", "item_id": "56c4761219:17", "text": "If set, this overrides the lens's circle of confusion. Note that this parameter currently only works with RIS and"}
{"id": "254bb97b57f12e1608fefc4517de768427b2fd6d2cffbbfcbc09f3c818198d5f", "item_id": "56c4761219:18", "text": "not"}
{"id": "c6547725b150ffb14c01047805ef389ee8dfae4e69d83e8ee4e927e40e9479a8", "item_id": "56c4761219:19", "text": "with XPU."}
